  <description><![CDATA[<p>The stunning building of Hotel Due Torri is steeped in history dating back to the fourteenth century where it started out as a palazzo. In 1958 the space was transformed into a luxury hotel by Enrico Walner, who designed and curated the interior with its fine pottery, original art and antique furniture. On the lower ground floor you’ll find the recently restored Arena Casarini fresco, a stunning work of art depicting the Opera seasons. Its luxurious and elegant feel is still prevalent today with its hand varnished parquet floors, marble, Murano glass chandeliers, mosaic work, wood panelling and luxurious fabrics creating a timeless ambiance. The hotel is a prime location to explore <a data-udi="umb://document/41229767036d47f28a27ac846e23458b" href="/{localLink:umb://document/41229767036d47f28a27ac846e23458b}" title="Verona">Verona</a> and its historic centre on foot. It is close to the river Adige, a few minutes from the central Piazze Erbe, five-minuets from the Verona’s Romanesque Cathedral and a ten-minute walk to the famous Roman Arena and its open-air <a data-udi="umb://document/31b4d81670c64b2e9ebbd962950ac8d2" href="/{localLink:umb://document/31b4d81670c64b2e9ebbd962950ac8d2}" title="Verona Opera">opera</a>.</p>
<p>Watch the sun glow over the red rooftops of the ancient city as it descends beneath the hilltops on the horizon, as you sip an evening aperitif or indulge in a delicious culinary experience from the Panoramic Terrace &amp; Grill Restaurant. The beautiful candlelit Due Tori Lounge &amp; Restaurant on the ground floor, serves delicious traditional Italian cuisine and is perfect for a pre opera meal.</p>
<p>Transfer time: approx. 25 mins by private car from Verona airport.</p>]]></description>
